public class FrameBodyUnsupported
extends AbstractID3v2FrameBody

Represents a framebody for a frame identifier that is not defined for the tag version. It is possible that the identifier is valid for a later version but not the version that this frame belongs to. If the identifier is valid for an earlier tag version but not this version then this class should not be used instead use FrameBodyDeprecated. The body consists of an array of bytes representing all the bytes in the body.
